  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is considered a criminal offense under legislation in most countries. Money laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. It is typically addressed in:\n\n1. Criminal codes\n2. Anti-money laundering (AML) laws\n3. Financial crime statutes\n\nPenalties can include:\n- Significant fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Additional criminal charges\n\nThe specific legal frameworks vary by jurisdiction, but money laundering is universally recognized as a serious criminal activity.",
